It can be narrowed to `DESCRIBE TABLE zipkin2.span;`

Mostly likely related to the unicode character [here](https://github.com/openzipkin/zipkin/blob/master/zipkin-storage/cassandra/src/main/resources/zipkin2-schema-indexes.cql#L43) used in the SASI. (Confirmed: if the delimiter is changed to any ascii character then cqlsh is happy to describe the span table.)

@drolando and @amitskatti I'm presuming that Zipkin otherwise is working fine for you?
